CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 17, 1976, pg. 17, reads: "Remember When... The fabulous Harlemites played throughout the Pittsburgh area? They were great musicians.  And their syncopated jazz was heard in some of the better niteries of that golden era.  in photo above, see if you can identify the members of the Harlemites.  One is probably the best-known jazz pianist in the country today. Remember?  Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of the Leroy Brown Orchestra at Harlem Casino. Leroy Brown on saxophone on left, Guy Hunter on saxophone on right, James "Honey Boy" Minor on drums, Joe Westray on keyboard, George "Ghost" Howell on bass, Erroll Garner on piano, William "Wimpie" Mosley on horn, Byron Garrison, Andrew "Pindy" Penn, Joe Porter and Dave Page, on stage in Harlem Casino with painted background of bandleader and dancers
